  compatibilityNotes: {
    ESTP:
      "Shared analytical engine but opposite energy orientation — their extraversion and your introversion create natural rhythm. They pull you into the world; you ground them with depth. Strong mutual respect for competence and practical skill. Risk: they may find your pace too slow; you may find their pace exhausting. Works when both respect the other's engagement style.",
    ESTJ:
      "Shared practical orientation but different authority structures — they trust established systems while you trust your own analysis. You'll clash when they say 'follow procedure' and you say 'this procedure doesn't work.' Works when they appreciate your diagnostic skill and you appreciate their organizational competence. Risk: mutual stubbornness disguised as principle.",
    ISFP:
      "Shared secondary function creates a bond through physical activity and present-moment awareness, but you process through logic while they process through values. They feel their way to decisions you'd analyze your way to. This difference is either complementary or maddening depending on the maturity of both parties. Deep potential for understanding if you learn each other's language.",
    INTJ:
      "Your logic engine plus their pattern recognition creates a powerful analytical partnership. They see where things are heading; you see how things actually work right now. Mutual respect for independence and competence. Risk: both operate primarily in your heads, and neither naturally initiates emotional connection — the relationship can become intellectually rich and emotionally sparse.",
    INFJ:
      "Maximum cognitive contrast — their Ni-Fe stack is your exact reverse. They see abstract patterns and navigate emotional landscapes that are your blind spot. You see concrete reality and solve practical problems that mystify them. Potentially the most growth-promoting pairing if both tolerate the discomfort of genuine difference. Risk: mutual incomprehension at a fundamental level.",
    ENFP:
      "Their extraverted intuition generates a volume of possibilities that your logic engine finds simultaneously fascinating and exhausting. They see connections everywhere; you want to verify each one. They need verbal processing; you need quiet analysis. The attraction is real — they bring warmth and ideas, you bring grounding and follow-through. Risk: they feel shut down by your silence; you feel overwhelmed by their need for engagement.",
    ENTJ:
      "Their strategic organizing paired with your tactical execution is a natural fit. They see the big picture and make the plan; you see the mechanical details and make it work. Mutual respect for competence and directness. Risk: their need to lead may clash with your need for autonomy. Works best when roles are clearly defined and they trust your domain expertise.",
    INTP:
      "Shared lead function creates deep intellectual understanding — you both run on internal logic engines. The difference: yours is grounded in physical reality while theirs operates in abstract theory. They build models; you build things. Excellent for intellectual companionship. Risk: two Ti-dominants can spend a lifetime in parallel intellectual tracks without ever building emotional intimacy.",
    ENFJ:
      "Their warmth and emotional leadership directly addresses your blind spot. They create the social and emotional environment that you wouldn't build yourself but genuinely thrive in. Risk: they may need more emotional reciprocity than you naturally provide, and their desire for harmony may feel like pressure to perform feelings you haven't processed yet.",
    ISFJ:
      "Their loyalty and practical care complement your independence and competence. They provide the steady emotional warmth and domestic stability that grounds your more restless tendencies. Risk: they may interpret your need for solitude as rejection, and your directness may wound their sensitivity. Works when both learn that different doesn't mean deficient.",
  },

